  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Vitamin D deficiency is common after bariatric surgery. This study is designed to determine
      if a high dose monthly supplement of vitamin D 3 will be effective in helping improve vitamin
      D status after surgery such as gastric bypass. Bariatric surgery subjects taking monthly high
      dose cholecalciferol supplements in addition to the standard vitamin D protocol will have a
      significant rise in serum vitamin D levels compared to the subjects taking only the usual
      vitamin D protocol.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
